76561197998717797,Recommended,313400,25558183,"Posted: 17 September, 2016",all,Khorne on the Kob,"Despite the thumbs up I want to make clear that this game is a mixed bag, and I think this game makes it clear that one good idea isn't enough to make a great game.First, the revolving mechanic, Yes it's cool, dodging bullets, lining up the enemy to wreck them, spotting background enemies. The revolver mechanic really makes the background a massive factor in the game. However, all of the enemies bullets are two dimensional. It's really hard to explain but think of it this way, you see off in the distance an enemy that is shooting a laser out, it looks like it's there to block your path but even though its far off in the background, if you move your ship in front of the laser, you will get hit by it. It can be really disorienting at times.Second, the ship is boring, you have 3 weapons, your standard shot that shoots directly infront of you, a laser that shoots right in front of you, and an EMP that shoots right in front of you(or clears all bullets on screen if you let it charge) Lasers turn yellow bullets into points, EMP turns anything into Points. But since you can't shoot anywhere but in front of you, you can't hit anything above or behind you. This wouldn't such a problem as long as things didn't attack from behind or above, but they do, a lot. It's just angering since there is almost nothing you can do about those enemies. What would be so wrong with having multiple weapons that shoot somewhere besides infront of you? Oh yes and inorder to hit background enemies you have to get close to them in order to shoot them, so if that thing shoots you from way back in the background it will hit you instantly and you'll be ""too close"" to dodge.Third, the arching paths is really a non factor, there is almost no difference between the different paths, I'm not sure why they included it. Do you want the tunnel full of enemies, or the other tunnel full of enemies, it makes almost no difference.The Graphics are very good for an indie title and the music is great, and the game comes with the sound track. It's well polished and has no bugs as far as I can see, it's not great but it's not bad either and the price they are asking is completely reasonable. An okay game with one cool mechanic, but not much else."
